            <div class="faq-a">S-corp election (Form 1120-S) under <a href="https://www.law.cornell.edu/uscode/text/26/1361" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">IRC Section 1361</a> structures founder income as W-2 reasonable compensation + K-1 distributions. Under <a href="https://selling-guide.fanniemae.com/sel/b3-3.4-02/analyzing-returns-partnership-or-s-corporation" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">B3-3.4-02</a>, combined W-2 + K-1 qualifies with 2-year averaging plus Form 1084 cash-flow addbacks at the S-corp level. S-corp election reduces self-employment tax exposure by limiting wages subject to FICA/Medicare to W-2 reasonable comp.</div>
